{"article_id":"DOaOjOiAAjaJCP33","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"LISTEN TO ARTICLE 3:55","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"SHARE THIS ARTICLE","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Share Tweet","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Post Email","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Terms of Trade is a daily newsletter","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that untangles a world","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"embroiled in trade wars .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Sign up here .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"Beijing wants a rollback in tariffs in its trade war with the U.S.","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"before China can feasibly agree to buy as much as $ 50 billion of American agriculture products","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"President Donald Trump claims","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"are part of an initial deal ,","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"people familiar with the matter said .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Chinese officials are willing to start purchasing more U.S. agricultural products as part of the \" phase one \" trade deal ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"but it is not likely to reach the $ 40 billion to $ 50 billion","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"touted by Trump","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"under current circumstances ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"the people said ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"asking not to be identified","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"discussing the private negotiations .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"China ' s tit-for-tat tariffs on American agricultural products make it more expensive for its firms to import the goods .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Beijing would have to lift those levies","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"to make it easier to buy as much as $ 50 billion of goods ,","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"but would only do so","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"if the U.S. reciprocates","depth":14},{"id":26,"text":"and lifts its tariffs on Chinese goods ,","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"the people said .","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"Beijing has in the past granted waivers","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"so that its companies can buy U.S. farm goods","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"without paying Chinese tariffs .","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"It could do that again","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"to get purchases started ,","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"the people said .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"However , waivers are seen as being impractical for volumes as large as $ 50 billion a year ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"one of the people said .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"The condition highlights how far apart Washington and Beijing remain ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"even after reaching the handshake accord","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"touted by the U.S. last week .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Washington had said","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"China ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"which imported about $ 20 billion of U.S. farm goods in 2017 ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"agreed to make large agricultural purchases in exchange for relief on upcoming tariffs .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Beijing ' s position makes a deal more complex","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"than initially described .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Donald Trump shakes hands with Liu He in the Oval Office on Oct. 11 .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"Photographer :","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Andrew Harrer/","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"U.S. equity futures pared gains on the news","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"and the yen extended an advance ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"as investor optimism waned about prospects for a trade deal between the world ' s two largest economies .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Under the terms of the partial trade arrangement , Chinese spending on U.S. farm goods will scale to an annual figure of $ 40 billion to $ 50 billion over two years ,","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said earlier .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Chinese firms have bought U.S. agricultural products","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"including 20 million tons of soybeans and 700,000 tons of pork","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"so far this year","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"and will accelerate its purchases ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Geng Shuang told reporters on Tuesday .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"Asked about the \" phase one \" trade deal ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"he said","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"that what the U.S. said is \" accurate \"","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"and the U.S. and China have the same understanding of the situation .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"Both sides have expressed a willingness","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"to work toward a final agreement ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"and the attitudes of both sides are \" actually the same , \"","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"according to commentary","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"posted on the China Radio website .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Read More :","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"China Wants More Talks","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"Before Signing Trade Deal With Trump","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"The two sides are working toward a deal","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"that can be signed at the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation summit next month in Chile .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"China wants further talks as soon as the end of October","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"to hammer out the details ,","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"people familiar said separately earlier .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"Mnuchin also told CNBC","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"he expects officials to work in coming weeks","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"to get the first stage ready for both sides to sign .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"If that doesn ' t happen ,","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"new U.S. import levies on Chinese products will be imposed","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"starting Dec. 15 ,","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"China is considering buying a wide array items","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"to boost imports ,","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"including soybeans , cereals , cotton , ethanol , fertilizer , juice , coffee and meat ,","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"the people said ,","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"and it could also lift barriers on distillers dried grains","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"and remove a ban on chicken imports .","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"Machinery , lumber and pesticides could also be added ,","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"they said .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"The people said","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"these purchases would be worth more than $ 40 billion","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"but said","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"China hasn ' t decided on specific values for the items .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"China ' s Ministry of Commerce did not immediately respond to a fax","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"seeking comment on potential U.S. farm purchases .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Beijing adopted hefty anti-dumping and anti-subsidy tariffs on U.S. distillers dried grains , a by-product of corn ethanol production","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"that ' s used in animal feed ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"in 2017 .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"Axing the distillers dried grains tariffs would allow China , the world ' s biggest buyer , to resume purchases from the top supplier in a trade","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"once worth $ 2 billion","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"before falling to almost zero .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"It also still has retaliatory tariffs on products","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"including U.S. soybeans , corn and pork .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"Read More :","depth":4},{"id":105,"text":"China ' s Shopping List in America Has These Farm Goods at the Top","depth":4},{"id":106,"text":"- With assistance by Shuping Niu , Steven Yang , Isis Almeida , Jenny Leonard , and Dandan Li","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":212,"right":106,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent